Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery bowl or cup; light brown clay with some silver mica; interior glazed with traces of added bands; reserved on exterior, save for slight remains of glaze at top; inscription on the outside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.369)
